      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted with porcine blood analog (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 cP ± 0.1 cP at 37 °C). Flow rates controlled to ±2 % via Coriolis meter; rotational speed controlled to ±0.5 % via servo drive. All conditions logged and traceable to calibration records."
